The staff really hurt my heart as they laughed and talked amongst themselves even with other people in the store. I recommend to anyone and everyone please do not go in there unless you speak spanish. They discriminated against me because I'm a black man who just happens to speak spanish fluently. Sweetgreen is my favorite lunch place in Silver Spring. They are a bit pricey for a salad (expect to pay about $9 per), but their salads are amazing, and in my opinion, worth it. As a vegetarian, I appreciate their veggie salads, especially the Chic-p, which I get most often. They also have reusable salad holders that you can buy and reuse each time you go. Also, their utensils are compostable, which is pretty cool. In general, the people there are very friendly and nice.
